<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1440,1079,1140]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1079,1105]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Only in the members of this small 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1818" box="[713,780,1080,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[713,780,1080,1106]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Axina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (about 
<quantity box="[952,1055,1079,1106]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5 –7 mm</quantity>
) is there a yellow angular fascia in front of the middle of an otherwise dark brown to black elytral disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[191,1440,1155,1385]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,363,1155,1181]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[370,413,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Size</emphasis>
. Length 6.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[685,774,1155,1182]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[785,844,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[923,1015,1155,1182]" captionStart="Figures 114–117" captionStartId="69.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@69.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="Figures 114–117. Habitus of Axina species. 114) Axina conspicua. 115) A. equestris. 116) A. ignota. 117) A. ordinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565039/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1026,1087,1155,1181]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Color</emphasis>
. Dorsum dark brown; antenna, venter and legs testaceous. 
<emphasis box="[488,547,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/ FW 30/10. 
<emphasis box="[313,391,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 65/100; elytra, asetiferous punctures substriate, punctures extend slightly beyond elytral middle, width of interstitial spaces variable; EL/EW 260/45. 
<emphasis box="[377,483,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Female pygidium shallowly trilobed along distal margin, female visible abdominal sternite VI with recurved flap at distal margin; aedeagus, phallobasic lobes very short and contiguous; phallic plates serrate at both edges; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1440,1400,1460]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,310,1400,1426]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Variation.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[321,364,1401,1427]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Size</emphasis>
: Length 5.0–7.0 mm; width 1.0– 
<quantity box="[756,850,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. The brown markings on the elytron disc vary in conspicuousness.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1139,1476,1503]" box="[192,1139,1476,1503]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,376,1476,1502]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[702,780,1476,1502]" name="Bolivia" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
during October and November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
